imals, and minerals the California Indians used for food, basketry and cordage, medicine, and more. At a time when we are grappling with the problems of maintaining habitat diversity and sustainable economies, we find that these native peoples and their traditions have much to teach us about the future, as well as the past, of California.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aHunting and gathering societieszCalifornia. 0aIndians of North AmericaxHuntingzCalifornia. 0aIndians of North AmericazCaliforniaxSocial life and customs. 7aNATURE / General.2bisacsh  abasketry.  abiological diversity.  acalifornia.  aceremony.  achiefs.  acordage.  acultural diversity.  acultural history.  adances.  adiversity.  aenvironmental sciences.  aenvironmentalism.  aethnobiology.  aethnobotany.  afeasts.  afire.  afood.  aindigenous cultures.  aindigenous peoples.  aindigenous religions.  amaster craftspeople.  amedicine.  amigration.  anative americans in california.  anative americans.  anative californians.  anatural environment.  anatural resources.  asustainability.  aunited states of america.1 aLightfoot, Kent G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPanich, Lee M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aParrish, Otis, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aSchneider, Tsim D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSoluri, K. Elizabeth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052024471940uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094228840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520942288423Coveruhttps://www.d